import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['volume'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', label='Median Volume: {:.2f}'.format(data['volume'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily volume traded?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of the closing price over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['open'], data['close'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Open')
    plt.ylabel('Close')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['difference'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['difference'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily price differences?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
